<br>
Number of Turns - Not exactly sure, probably between 6 and 8<br>
<br>
Table 1 - (Chaos - 3000 total pts, Imperials - 3500 + reserves) The Chaos forces objective is to kill an Inquisitor and retinue (hopefully supplied by Rus).  These will be on the main table surrounded by Jim's forces and then flanked by Wayne and myself (3500 points total among us).  Barclay and Ken will be allied against us with a total of 3000 points between them.  They will have sustained attack, but once a unit is recycled, Dave (if there) and Nathan's forces will arrive to assist the Imperium.<br>
<br>
Table 2 - (Merle - 2000 pts, 1000 in Heavy, 1000 in other; Keith - 1000 and Rus 1000) Merle is serving as the Chaos artillery battery, Keith and Rus are trying to take it out.  Merle will be able to fire Ordnance weapons onto main table and Rus and Keith may move onto the main table.<br>
<br>
Table 3 - (Derek - 1500pts, Johnny - 1000pts, Pyper - 500pts) Derek will be defending two power plants that are fueling the Imperial shield systems.  The problem is, 1)they stole it from the Tau and 2)a tyranid hive lies under the area.  Johnny tries to take out Derek with Pyper showing up on turn two between the two bunkers to assist.  Note: if Pyper can't make it, Johnny will just have to bring 1500 pts. <p>&quot;... whereever you rub it, it always feels better, ...&quot; - Brak<br>
