Enough!<br>
<br>
This isn't going to work.  It's too codified and not organized.  We've got to have some structure, but not get too complicated.  The KISS principle is going into effect (Keep It Simple Stupid, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Knights In Satan's Service.)<br>
<br>
There will be plenty of notices posted everywhere, and here's the first one of them:<br>
<br>
Anyone who can play on September 6th, go sign up to the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://gallopsstuff.com/mailman/listinfo/miniaturegame_gallopsstuff.com" target="top">Gallops Minatures Gaming Mailing List</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  If you have difficulties signing up through the website, you may send an email to <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:newsletter@gallopsstuff.com "> newsletter@gallopsstuff.com </a><!--EZCODE MAIL END-->with your name and email address and I'll sign you up myself.<br>
<br>
In order to play in the mega-battle, you <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">must</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> sign up by sending an email to <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:Miniaturegame@gallopsstuff.com"> Miniaturegame@gallopsstuff.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--><br>
stating your name, your army, and the maximum amount of <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">painted</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> points you can bring.  (See below regarding the restrictions on painting.)<br>
<br>
The game(s) will run from 11AM - 7PM on Saturday, September 6.  Please arrive between 10AM - 10:30AM.<br>
<br>
The Megabattle will be a post-campaign event.  This will allow us some freedom where we can have same-side squabbles (if one side outnumbers) but no one has to feel like they lost for their team.  The Megabattle will take place on several tables, some of which will contain multiple people per side, some of which will contain a single person on each side.<br>
<br>
All players will be notified before hand as to who their teammates (if applicable) and their opponent(s) will be, their mission for their table, and any special rules/or events they may be allowed as part of the narrative.  To restate, all players will have this knowledge provided to them <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">before they arrive at the store on Saturday!</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
If you cannot play on Saturday, September 6, or have not signed up for the Megabattle by the deadline, we're sorry, but an event of this sort requires pre-planning and commitment on behalf of both the staff and players.  We apologize for this restriction.  Gallops Comics and Games will be holding many miniature gaming events allowing for walk-in players in the future.  All interested parties are invited to watch and cheer/jeer for their favorite side!<br>
<br>
If your forces are unpainted, we're sorry, but pictures of this event will be submitted to the Heavyhand.org website, the Gallopsstuff.com website, and White Dwarf magazine.  We apologize for this restriction.  Gallop's Comics and Games will be holding many miniature gaming events allowing for unpainted miniatures in the future.  All interested parties are invited to watch and cheer/jeer for their favorite side!<br>
<br>
At the end of the day, the victor will be determined between the Forces of Order and the Forces of Disorder.  Each side will then vote for their Most Valuable Player by criteria of their own choosing in a secret ballot.  The winner for each side will recieve a special piece of wargear that they may use with that particular army during any future Gallops Comics and Games 40K event, including any Rogue Traders or store tournaments we run later!  (We won't tell Games Workshop if you won't.) <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;Because there is no wrong, there is no right<br>
 And I sleep <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">very</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> well at night.<br>
 No shame, no solution,<br>
 No remorse, no retribution&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=32><img src=http://heavyhand.org/buttonreply2.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub70.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</